
# No more than 72 chars ───────────────────────────── which is here -> #

# COMMIT TYPES
# ├─ feat:         adding or removing features
# ├─ fix:          bug fixes
# ├─ refactor:     code changes that neither fix a bug nor add a feature
# ├─ content:      adds content e.g. articles, videos, etc.
# ├─ docs:         changes to documentation
# ├─ revert:       reverts a previous commit
# └─ chore:        miscellaneous changes

############################ EXAMPLE COMMIT ############################
# feat(scope)!: add Feature to project
#
# This is an example body paragraph. The scope is an optional field to
# make a more specific commit. Be consistent in letter casing.
#
# This is another body paragraph, and below is the footer.
#
# BREAKING CHANGE: either this line or the "!" above are required
# Co-authored-by: Jane Doe
# Reviewed-by: John Doe
# Refs: #123
